The install / configure / wrapper flow in this plugin's `backend.ts` is
ported from `decky-lsfg-vk` — specifically the GitHub-release download,
zip extraction into `~/.local/{lib,share/vulkan/implicit_layer.d}/`,
`library_path` rewrite in the layer JSON, `~/.config/lsfg-vk/conf.toml`
serialization, and the executable `~/lsfg` wrapper script that exports
`LSFG_PROCESS` and execs the game. UI surface, per-Steam-appId override
shape, and the rest of our plugin scaffold are original. Both ports
and originals ship under the BSD-3-Clause; the upstream copyright
notice and BSD-3-Clause disclaimer are preserved in
`THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md` per BSD-3 §1 and §2.

## 2. Frame-generation runtime (downloaded at runtime, not bundled)

  https://github.com/PancakeTAS/lsfg-vk
  License: GPL-3.0 (see https://github.com/PancakeTAS/lsfg-vk/blob/develop/LICENSE.md)

This plugin downloads `lsfg-vk_noui.zip` from PancakeTAS/lsfg-vk's
GitHub Releases at user request (see `RELEASES_API` in `backend.ts`)
and extracts `liblsfg-vk.so` + the layer JSON into the user's home
directory. **The `lsfg-vk` runtime is not redistributed by this
repository or its release artifacts.** The user fetches it directly
from the upstream's official distribution, and the GPL-3.0 governs
the on-disk artifact on the user's machine — not this plugin's source.

This is the same orchestration pattern used by `plugins/deck-dictation`
for Handy. Distribution of the runtime is upstream's responsibility;
this plugin is only an installer + UI + config writer.

The frame-generation feature itself depends on the user owning a
copy of "Lossless Scaling" (the proprietary Windows application);
this plugin detects `Lossless.dll` at the default Steam library path
and accepts a custom override. Lossless Scaling is third-party
proprietary software and is not affiliated with or licensed by this
project.
